comparison to other european banks ubs suffered among the largest losses during the subprime mortgage crisis and it was required to raise large amounts of outside capital the bank received a us billion capital injection in  from the government of singapore investment corporation currently gic private limited effective from july  which remains one of the banks largest shareholders ubs also received capital from the swiss government further complemented by a series of equity offerings in   and  contents  corporate structure  corporate center  ubs wealth management  ubs europe se  ubs wealth management americas  ubs personal  corporate banking  ubs asset management  ubs investment bank  competition  ubs graduate talent programs  history  swiss bank corporation  origins and early years –  postwar years –  union bank of switzerland  origins and early years –  activities in world war ii  postwar years –  merger of union bank of switzerland and swiss bank corporation  the failure of long term capital management ltcm  rising in the ranks –  the beginning of ubs troubles subprime mortgage crisis   impact of the financial crisis –  stabilizing the ship –present  acquisition history  corporate governance  board of directors  group executive board  shareholders  controversies  holocaust assets s–  us trade embargoes –  indian stock market crash –  us discrimination lawsuits –  us tax evasion –   rogue trader scandal –  lehman brothers notes –  us municipal bond market rigging –  arms sales and indian money laundering –  libor benchmark rigging –  currency benchmark rigging –   us mortgagebacked securities –  french tax evasion –   german tax evasion –   belgian tax evasion –   timber corruption and malaysian money laundering –   forex manipulation scandal –  puerto rico bond funds  panama papers –   corporate social responsibility  recognition  sponsorship  sports  culture  recent developments and outlook  see also  further reading  references  external links corporate structureedit ubs is a jointstock company aktiengesellschaft pursuant to swiss laws its shares are listed at the six swiss exchange and the new york stock exchange nyse as of february  ubs is present in all major financial centers worldwide having offices in  countries with about  of its approx  employees working in the americas  in switzerland  in europe the middle east and africa and  in the asia pacific region the bank has its major presence in the united states its american headquarters for investment banking are located in new york city for private wealth management in weehawken new jersey and its sales  trading headquarters can be found in stamford connecticut ubs wma headquarters at lincoln harbor in weehawken nj the companys global business groups are i wealth management ii investment banking and iii asset management additionally ubs is the leading provider of retail banking and commercial banking services in switzerland as established already in  overall invested assets are chf  billion shareholders equity is chf  billion and market capitalization is chf  billion by the end of  in november  the shares in ubs group ag were listed and started trading as a new holding company on the nyse and six swiss exchange upon application and with the effect as of  january  the shares of the usb ag the subsidiary of the ubs group ag were delisted from the nyse ubs structure includes five divisions in total wealth management wealth management americas personal  corporate banking asset management investment bank starting already on  june  all ubs business groups including ubs paine webber and ubs warburg were rebranded under the ubs moniker following companys start of operations as a unified global entity corporate centeredit corporate center focuses on the group’s control functions which are mainly finance risk control and legal all logistics and support services are also located with this division and include operations information technology human resources communications physic