demark of the wikimedia foundation inc a nonprofit organization privacy policy about wikipedia disclaimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view ubs  wikipedia ubs from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search for other uses see ubs disambiguation ubs group ag type aktiengesellschaft ag public company traded as six ubsg six ubsn nyse ubs industry banking financial services predecessor union bank of switzerland and swiss bank corporation merged in  painewebber merged in  founded   years ago  headquarters zürich basel area served worldwide key people axel a weber chairman sergio ermotti ceo products investment banking investment management wealth management private banking corporate banking private equity finance and insurance consumer banking mortgages credit cards operating income chf  billion  total assets chf  billion  total equity chf  billion  number of employees   capital ratio    website ubscom ubs ag is a swiss global financial services company incorporated in the canton of zurich and coheadquartered in zürich and basel the company provides wealth management asset management and investment banking services for private corporate and institutional clients worldwide and is generally considered to be a bulge bracket bank in switzerland these services are also offered to retail clients the name ubs was originally an abbreviation for the union bank of switzerland but it ceased to be a representational abbreviation after the banks merger with the swiss bank corporation in  the company traces its origins to  when the earliest of its predecessor banks was founded ubs has over chf  trillion in invested assets and remains a leading provider of retail banking and commercial banking services in switzerland it is the biggest bank in switzerland operating in more than  countries with  employees around the world as of  in comparison to other european banks ubs suffered among the largest losses during the subprime mortgage crisis and it was required to raise large amounts of outside capital the bank received a us billion capital injection in  from the government of singapore investment corporation currently gic private limited effective from july  which remains one of the banks largest shareholders ubs also received capital from the swiss government further complemented by a series of equity offerings in   and  contents  corporate structure  corporate center  ubs wealth management  ubs europe se  ubs wealth management americas  ubs personal  corporate banking  ubs asset management  ubs investment bank  competition  ubs graduate talent programs  history  swiss bank corporation  origins and early years –  postwar years –  union bank of switzerland  origins and early years –  activities in world war ii  postwar years –  merger of union bank of switzerland and swiss bank corporation  the failure of long term capital management ltcm  rising in the ranks –  the beginning of ubs troubles subprime mortgage crisis   impact of the financial crisis –  stabilizing the ship –present  acquisition history  corporate governance  board of directors  group executive board  shareholders  controversies  holocaust assets s–  us trade embargoes –  indian stock market crash –  us discrimination lawsuits –  us tax evasion –   rogue trader scandal –  lehman brothers notes –  us municipal bond market rigging –  arms sales and indian money laundering –  libor benchmark rigging –  currency benchmark rigging –   us mortgagebacked securities –  french tax evasion –   german tax evasion –   belgian tax evasion –   timber corruption and malaysian money laundering –   forex manipulation scandal –  puerto rico bond funds  panama papers –   corporate social responsibility  recognition  sponsorship  sports  culture  recent developments and outlook  see also  further reading  references  external links corporate structureedit ubs is a jointstock company aktiengesellschaft pursuant to swiss laws its shares are listed at the six swiss exchange and the new york stock exchange nyse as of february  ubs is present in all major financial centers worldwide having offices in  countries with about  of its approx  employees working in the americas  in switzerland  in europe the middle east and africa and  in the asia pacific region the bank has its major presence in the united states its american headquarters for investment banking are located in new york city for private wealth management in weehawken new jersey and its sales  trading headquarters can be found in stamford connecticut ubs wma headquarters at lincoln harbor in weehawken nj the companys global business groups are i wealth management ii investment banking and iii asset management additionally ubs is the leading provider of retail banking and commercial banking services in switzerland as established already in  overall invested assets are chf  billion shareholders equity is chf  billion and market capitalization is chf  billion by the end of  in november  the shares in ubs group ag were listed and started trading as a new holding company on the nyse and six swiss exchange upon application and with the effect as of  january  the shares of the usb ag the subsidiary of the ubs group ag were delisted from the nyse ubs structure includes five divisions in total wealth management wealth management americas personal  corporate banking asset management investment bank starting already on  june  all ubs business groups including ubs paine webber and ubs warburg were rebranded under the ubs moniker following companys start of operations as a unified global entity corporate centeredit corporate center focuses on the group’s control functions which are mainly finance risk control and legal all logistics and support services are also located with this division and include operations information technology human resources communications physical security and information security ubs wealth managementedit ubss wealth management division offers highnetworth individuals around the world with the exception of those served by the division of wealth management americas a range of advisory and investment products and services as of the end of  ubs wealth managements invested assets totaled chf  billion the whole companies assets under management aum amounted to us  billion in  representing a  decrease in aum compared to the equivalent data of  more than  of total invested assets in ubs wealth management belong to individuals with a networth of chf  million or more of the remaining  of total invested assets  of the total belong to individuals with networth between chf  million and chf  million and the last  of total assets belong to individuals with a networth of less than chf  million ubs offers brokerage services and products as well as asset management and other investment advisory and portfolio management products and services additionally ubs provides a broad range of securities and savings products that are supported by the firms underwriting and research activities as well as order execution and clearing services for transactions originated by individual investors the business is further divided geographically with separate businesses focused on the us and other international markets twothirds of the total invested assets come from europe and switzerland with the final onethird coming mainly from the asiapacific region with its headquarters in switzerland ubs wealth management is present in nearly  countries with approximately  offices  of which are in switzerland as of the end of  around  people worldwide were employed by ubs wealth management in switzerland ubs swiss bank provides a complete set of retail banking services that includes checking savings credit cards and mortgage products for individuals they offer cash management and commercial banking services for small businesses and corporate clients as well ubs europe seedit ubs europe se headquarters in frankfurt am main hesse in the end of  ubs founded a  owned eu